♪Convincing myself it has nothing to do
with joy or sorrow♪

192
00:13:52,901 --> 00:13:57,472
♪Later I met someone like you♪

193
00:13:57,978 --> 00:14:00,912
♪But it wasn't you♪

194
00:14:25,040 --> 00:14:27,269
♪Is it really that easy♪

195
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:29,280
(From childhood,)

196
00:14:29,280 --> 00:14:30,960
(protecting you has been my only mission.)

197
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:33,120
Go!

198
00:14:37,760 --> 00:14:39,240
(I saw the person I trusted the most)

199
00:14:41,160 --> 00:14:42,920
(turn into a man-eating ghost.)

200
00:14:42,920 --> 00:14:44,160
(Yue,)

201
00:14:44,160 --> 00:14:46,040
(I'm already in hell.)

202
00:14:46,040 --> 00:14:47,600
(You don't need to fall with me.)

203
00:14:49,880 --> 00:14:51,760
(Fu Yunzheng, I like you.)

204
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:54,400
(A sister will always be a sister.)

205
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:56,040
(And a brother will always
be a brother.)

206
00:14:56,920 --> 00:14:59,000
(You treat me as your possession,)

207
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:01,600
(not allowing me near other men,)

208
00:15:02,680 --> 00:15:04,840
(but you don't respond to my feelings.)

209
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:06,840
(I won't allow you
to marry another man.)

210
00:15:10,640 --> 00:15:12,360
(I wish I could go back
to your childhood)

211
00:15:13,160 --> 00:15:15,000
(and open the cellar door for you.)

212
00:15:15,480 --> 00:15:16,840
(You've already opened it.)

213
00:15:23,280 --> 00:15:24,280
(What did you wish for?)

214
00:15:28,080 --> 00:15:29,600
(I hope that one day)

215
00:15:36,080 --> 00:15:38,120
(we can be together forever and ever.)

216
00:15:41,210 --> 00:15:44,544
♪But it wasn't you♪

217
00:16:00,140 --> 00:16:02,420
♪As winter evenings grow darker♪

218
00:16:02,420 --> 00:16:05,620
♪When the air itself feels restless♪

219
00:16:07,380 --> 00:16:10,020
♪When the hand that once held mine♪

220
00:16:10,020 --> 00:16:12,780
♪Is no longer warm♪

221
00:16:13,060 --> 00:16:16,620
♪When memories gradually♪

222
00:16:16,620 --> 00:16:19,980
♪Lose their brilliance♪

223
00:16:20,660 --> 00:16:25,660
♪Fireworks fall, and the night
crumbles into ruin♪

224
00:16:29,380 --> 00:16:31,780
♪When neon lights outside the car window
are vibrant♪

225
00:16:31,780 --> 00:16:34,540
♪When you said you liked them♪

226
00:16:36,500 --> 00:16:39,260
♪When the summer night sky lit up♪

227
00:16:39,260 --> 00:16:41,020
♪The loneliness of the night♪

228
00:16:41,780 --> 00:16:45,900
♪When your gaze begins to avoid mine♪

229
00:16:45,900 --> 00:16:49,340
♪When it all becomes unbearable♪

230
00:16:49,460 --> 00:16:51,340
♪When the story ends♪

231
00:16:51,860 --> 00:16:55,980
♪When the dialogue fades,
and what was said still lingers♪

232
00:16:56,540 --> 00:16:58,940
♪I remember every answer you gave♪

233
00:16:58,940 --> 00:17:00,660
♪All the habits we shared♪

234
00:17:00,780 --> 00:17:04,100
♪Unwilling to part, leaving no regrets♪

235
00:17:04,100 --> 00:17:08,060
♪Out of a hundred encounters,
only one is lucky enough♪

236
00:17:08,060 --> 00:17:11,020
♪To find the right bond♪

237
00:17:11,020 --> 00:17:13,180
♪When there's still a chance
for a different ending♪

238
00:17:13,180 --> 00:17:14,940
♪When you begin to warm♪

239
00:17:15,220 --> 00:17:18,180
♪When I remain courageous♪

240
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:20,220
♪When I still remember♪

241
00:17:20,660 --> 00:17:25,340
♪When you still like me♪
